Business Day’s Mudiwa Gavaza spoke to one of Nedbank’s long-term clients in the downstream fuel trade. Branching into the global trade arena, the business owner explained, has slowed down payments, putting his company’s new global venture in a tricky position. Nedbank Business Banking’s divisional head for global trade sales, Lazarus Devasagayam, shares three factors that help Nedbank’s global trade specialists understand their clients’ transactions to help mitigate the associated risks and structure the right solutions. Listen to the podcast: Visit the Nedbank Business Banking website for more information. This article was paid for by Nedbank Business Banking.